radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated appendix with mural enhancement and surrounding fatty stranding, measuring up to 10 mm, fails to fill with oral contrast. Mild atelectasis at the left lung base. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax. Liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, large and small bowel appear normal. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No suspicious osseous lesions.
